\begin_layout Section
Preamble
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Following is an analysis of seismographic measurements conducted in January 2026 at the Physical Oceanography in Multiple Scales (POMS) lab.
 The report covers daily variability,
 channel-to-channel differences,
 and some noise distributions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The 
\series bold
goal
\series default
 of the analysis was to estimate the mechanical spectrum of the environment toward conducting experiments in capillary wave sensing by optical camera in a tabletop aquarium.
 We wanted to understand whether the background noise would drown our signal of down to 100
\begin_inset Formula $\mu m$
\end_inset

 high ripples.
 The expected velocity and acceleration of the capillary waves should be about the velocity and acceleration of the wedge plunger that will excite them,
 i.e.
 at the order of 
\begin_inset Formula $10\frac{mm}{s}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $1000\frac{mm}{s^{2}}$
\end_inset

,
 respectively.
\end_layout

