 at their high positions,
 present 
\begin_inset Formula $Z$
\end_inset

-axis vibrations much stronger than 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $E$
\end_inset

 vibrations.
 The disparity vanished once the seismographs were moved to the floor,
 suggesting that both supporting structures (table,
 cabinet) amplify selectively vertical motion.
\end_layout

