 Jan.
 21.
 Note that only the morning hours were included because the marking at two o'clock skewed the overall RMS of the work hours this day.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Few remarks about the spectral distributions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
First,
 we also see how work hours background noise can be much higher than the high-end earth base depicted by the upper gray lines (Peterson's high).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Second,
 the low tail that crosses the lower gray line (Peterson's low) is attributed to sensor response.
\end_layout

